Subject: [liste-egc] Academic Opportunities in Information Technology at
 Monash University, Melbourne

--001a1140ac3812220a055b2d84ca
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="UTF-8"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

The Faculty of Information Technology at Monash University wishes to
appoint outstanding academics in multiple areas of computer science and
information systems to join our world-class team to deliver high-quality
research and teaching which will help shape the future of computing.

We are currently recruiting in the following areas:

   - Data Science (including artificial intelligence, machine learning,
   modelling, optimisation and data visualisation)
   - Computer Systems (including networks, cloud computing, internet of
   things, software engineering and cybersecurity)
   - IT for Energy (computer scientists working on applications in energy)

Continuing full-time academic positions are available at Lecturer and
Senior Lecturer levels (equivalent to Assistant Professor and Associate
Professor in the US). Additionally, outstanding applicants in any area of
computer science and information systems at any level are also encouraged
to apply. The faculty offers a generous start-up package including
relocation, start-up research funds, scholarships for PhD students and a
reduced teaching load for the first two years.

The Faculty of Information Technology <https://www.monash.edu/it>  is in
the top 100 in the world for computer science (QS global rankings). We have
over 130 academics working in the areas of data science, cybersecurity,
creative technologies and human-computer interaction, and organisational
and social informatics. As a faculty, we value interdisciplinary research
with targeted growth in digital health research, IT for energy, and smart
futures. We are part of Monash University, one of Australia=E2=80=99s leadi=
ng
research-intensive universities, a member of the prestigious Group of
Eight, and ranked in the top 100 universities in the world. The faculty is
currently experiencing unprecedented growth; as such, there are substantial
opportunities for the right candidates.

The faculty is strongly committed to improving the diversity of our staff
and students, and promoting a culture of equity, fairness, respect and
openness. We fully support the principles of the Athena SWAN Charter.
Applications from female candidates are strongly encouraged.

Please visit our webpage for further information on the key areas in which
the Faculty of Information Technology is recruiting exceptional Academics:
https://www.monash.edu/it/about-us/recruiting-exceptional-academics

*Please note*: The Faculty of Information Technology reserves the right to
make one or multiple appointments to any or all of the above positions.

*Location*: Clayton campus

*Employment Type:* Full-time

*Duration: *Continuing appointments

*Remuneration: *$95,297 - $113,166 pa Level B / $116,737 - $134,606 pa
Level C (plus 17% employer superannuation)
http://careers.pageuppeople.com/513/cw/en/job/568422/academic-opportunities=
-in-information-technology

--=20
Dr Germain Forestier
